<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-471-425  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 471 425.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Sept 10 1990 v29 n18 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New study: electromagnetic fields hazardous?andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dooley, Bill.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Electronics manufacturers should take the lead in protectingworkers from the possible hazards of electromagnetic fields,according to a report in the Oct 1990 IEEE Spectrum.andP;  The exacthazards are not currently known, but government agencies may forceemployers to take action if they do not take the initiativethemselves.andP;  The authors of the report warn that studies beingconducted in the 1990s will reveal significant health risksassociated with electromagnetic fields.andP;  They recommend thatmanufacturers redesign electrical systems to protect the public.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electromagnetic FieldsRisk AnalysisReportsPublic HealthGovernment Regulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>